                <h2 class=3D""><span id=3D"convert-to-feet-per-minute" styl=
e=3D"scroll-margin-top: 100px;">Convert to Feet per Minute</span></h2>
                                <div class=3D"slide-key" data-post-url=3D"/=
convert-mph-feet-per-second-2306812/" data-post-title=3D"How To Convert MPH=
 To Feet Per Second" data-slide-num=3D"" data-post-id=3D"12954592">
                </div>
				            <div class=3D"columns-holder ">
                <h2 class=3D"subheading">Convert to Feet per Minute</h2>
<p>Divide your speed in feet per hour by 60. This is the number of minutes =
in an hour. Therefore, the result is your speed in feet per minute. For exa=
mple, 316,800 feet per hour divided by 60 minutes per hour is 5,280 feet pe=
r minute.</p>

            </div>
            </div>

            <div class=3D"news-article" data-mrf-recirculation=3D"Article -=
 Text links" data-slot-rendered-content=3D"true">
               =20
                <h2 class=3D""><span id=3D"convert-to-feet-per-second" styl=
e=3D"scroll-margin-top: 100px;">Convert to Feet per Second</span></h2>
                                <div class=3D"slide-key" data-post-url=3D"/=
convert-mph-feet-per-second-2306812/" data-post-title=3D"How To Convert MPH=
 To Feet Per Second" data-slide-num=3D"" data-post-id=3D"12954592">
                </div>
				            <div class=3D"columns-holder ">
                <h2 class=3D"subheading">Convert to Feet per Second</h2>
<p>Divide your speed in feet per minute by 60. This is the number of second=
s in a minute. Therefore, the result is your speed in feet per second. For =
example, 5,280 feet per minute divided by 60 seconds in a minute equals 88 =
feet per second.</p>
